Description:
Affordable entry to central Coburg!
This wonderful three bedroom home has been updated and is ready to move into now. Situated a few minutes stroll to Central Coburg shopping, Coburg Rail Station and Sydney Road tram, this home is in a great location that is close to schools, Coburg Lake and Pentridge Village.
Accommodation Includes:
• Formal entrance hallway
• Spacious formal lounge room
• Updated kitchen with meals area, stone benchtops, Gas cooking and dishwasher
• Sizeable master bedroom with walk in robe and full ensuite bathroom
• Two more spacious bedrooms (one with BIR)
• Central bathroom with separate shower and bathtub
• Separate W/C
• Full sized laundry
• Wide side drive
Featuring: Gas ducted heating, evaporative cooling, polished timber floors throughout, dishwasher and covered entertaining at rear.
The perfect home for first home buyers, downsizers who want to stay in the area or investors that are looking for a quality home in a central location with no money to spend.
Insights: 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Street Frontage Unit in Superb Location
This delightfully presented, fresh & inviting unit will appeal to first home buyers and investors alike.
Comprising 2 bedrooms, neat kitchen with 900mm stainless steel upright oven, meals area, separate lounge with gas heating, central bathroom with shower over bath and a compact sunny courtyard.
In a quality complex of only 4, with single carport (and visitor car spaces too) and located in a quiet yet particularly convenient location handy to Sydney Road Tram, cafes, shops, Coburg Station as well as Upfield Bike Path.
This truly is a wonderful opportunity for first home buyers or savvy investors.
Inspection By Appointment - Enquire Today!

Description:
A Sanctuary in the heart of Coburg
Mere steps to the cafes, restaurants and shops that make Sydney Rd such a sought-after destination the scale and style that define this townhouse residence brilliantly accentuate its individuality, a trait additionally enhanced by its street frontage. Double robes and ensuite privacy to the downstairs master bedroom precede open plan living where entertaining possibilities are eagerly anticipated. Integrated Smeg appliances and stone surfaces exemplify kitchen quality, while the option to enjoy meals alfresco is a welcome accompaniment - and undeniably attractive owing to the lush climbing jasmine that surrounds the decked courtyard. Upstairs bedrooms bask in the natural light captured by sky windows crowning dramatic vaulted ceilings. Private balcony to front bedroom, polished hardwood floors, ample storage and the convenience of car port plus extra off street parking. Moments to any form of transport including tram or train.

Description:
Urban Lifestyle, Parkland Surrounds
Set adjacent Merri Creek parklands, with the Nicholson Street tram at your door this two bedroom apartment offers an exceptional low maintenance lifestyle where urban living and parklands combine. Modern and spacious, boasting substantial living and dining, galley styled stone topped kitchen featuring Blanco appliances and sweet balcony overlooking the park, it presents oversized light filled living. Double bedrooms with BIR's, one with private balcony share a stylishly fitted bathroom that together with Euro laundry, secure entry, split system heating/cooling, car space and storage cage assure comfort and security. Ideally located to buses and trams, walking distance to Coburg Station, vibrant Sydney Road cafes, shopping and Coburg Leisure Centre, it proves a savvy first home or astute addition to any investment portfolio.

Description:
Renovated, refined, reborn
Masterfully remodelled to create a sublime four bedroom, two bathroom home for the modern family, this totally transformed Californian Bungalow combines large, luminous spaces with assured style. Beyond big bright bedrooms and chic designer bathrooms, including an ensuite, the home opens into a vast gourmet kitchen/dining/living. Boasting 900mm Ilve appliances, abundant custom cabinetry and expansive stone surfaces, it's linked to a deck, garden and wide carport accessing a rear ROW. With interior design by nene&uke and transformed by Calibre Built Developments, this stunning abode also features a front driveway, alarm, reverse cycle ducted heating/cooling, high ceilings, insulation, double glazing and 6-star energy rating. Trams, shops, Bush Reserve, CityLink access and schools are all nearby.

Poise and Potential in Coburg's Premier Pocket
"NENAGH" - all the ingredients needed for an inspired renovation and extension (STCA), this classic Californian presents a value-packed lifestyle opportunity in a sublime tree-lined streetscape - moments from Merri Creek trails and parkland. Beyond its attractive facade, the home's current floorplan comprises two main bedrooms and formal dining/third bedroom, functional bathroom, separate lounge through to the sunroom/meals area and adjoining kitchen. Description:
Quality, Designer Style and Every Luxury
Californian bungalow beauty and the finest transformation offer a lifestyle home like no other. Created with exceptional attention to every detail, this is a home you’ll be proud to own. Original heritage character is enhanced with a state-of-the-art renovation, featuring spectacular living spaces, three bedrooms, and deluxe kitchen and bathrooms. The home of a master craftsman and interior designer, every finish and feature is first-class. Superb family room is refined and stylish, and the adjoining large outdoor room is spectacular. Designed for all-weather living and large-scale entertaining, it features a wall of banquette seating, cast-iron fireplace, automated blinds, extensive storage, and integrated barbecue. Every room reveals impeccable planning, including the kitchen with premium appliances, timber and Caesarstone Raw Concrete benches, and spotted gum floors. The luxe ensuite and bathroom are finished to perfection, and every bedroom has custom-designed joinery. Beautiful landscaping, three-car garage and two off-street parking spaces, roof storage and hi-tech security features simply enhance this quality home.

Description:
Compelling Character In Coveted Locale
Uniting big, beautifully lit spaces with individual character and a cool aesthetic, this renovated three bedroom Californian Bungalow style home boasts dual street frontage in the esteemed Glencairn Estate. Soaring ceilings and thoughtful design maximise the feeling of space while majestic bay windows welcome in a wealth of light. Comprising a lounge/fourth bedroom, modern kitchen starring a 900mm Ilve gas stove with double oven and a living/meals domain, the floor plan is friendly and open. Impressively proportioned bedrooms share two bathrooms, complemented by a powder room. Further appeal is added by a spacious covered entertaining area, landscaped gardens, ducted heating, evaporative cooling, video intercom, security cameras, Ethernet wiring, long driveway, large double garage or potential home office/teen retreat and extensive storage including a supremely sizeable attic. Situated on approximately 566m2 with additional frontage on Jessie Street, this attractive residence is close to schools and only a stroll to transport, parks and the restaurants, shops and cafes of lively Sydney Road.
Insights: 12 Glencairn Avenue, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Period Elegance with Extended Appeal
Perfectly positioned in one of Coburg's most attractive tree-lined streets, this captivating Californian Bungalow is sure to make a lasting impression with its fine period details, extended floorplan and close proximity to a range of lifestyle attractions. Instantly appealing with its picket-fenced garden and gorgeous facade, the home's spacious interior comprises three bedrooms (extra-large master with WIR and private ensuite), main bathroom with spa, vast open-plan living and dining areas complemented by a granite-bench kitchen with breakfast bar, stainless steel cooking appliances and double dishwasher. Other stand-out features include ducted heating and split-system a/c, high ceilings throughout and polished timber floors, plus decked/paved outdoor entertaining area and large carport with remote-control rollerdoor to ROW. Walking distance to popular primary schools (St Fidelis and Coburg West), local parks and public transport options, it's also close to Sydney Road cafes, restaurants and Coburg's renowned shopping precinct. Inner-urban family perfection!
Insights: 35 Phillips Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Historic Touches, Modern Appeal
Enriched with compelling historic details lending undeniable character and a fashionable aesthetic, this exceptional two bedroom residence can't help but impress. Opening into a kitchen, dining and living domain, the beautifully presented home immediately reveals distinctive flair with polished concrete flooring. To the rear a tasteful private courtyard features a deck and bluestone wall, and further highlights harking back to the origins of the building include richly coloured exposed brickwork and timber beams. Quality Miele cooking appliances team with a dishwasher, stone surfaces, deep soft touch drawers and solid timber cabinetry to ensure the custom-made kitchen is ready to help you host dinner parties. A spectacular moulded hardwood staircase leads to two double bedrooms that include built-in robes, the master features a study alcove, plus there's also a chic central bathroom and European laundry. Heating/cooling, an undercover car space and storage cage add the ideal finishing touches. A stroll to Coburg Lake, cafes, Sydney Road, schools and transport, this remarkable abode makes an excellent base or investment with contemporary allure.
Insights: 13 Industry Lane, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 58 other 2 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Promise and Potential in the Heart of Coburg!
On a substantial block of land complete with ROW at the rear, this freestanding period home provides an environment of immediate comfort along with outstanding opportunities for those looking to revive or renew (STCA). Immaculately presented throughout, the home's current accommodation includes two large bedrooms (one with BIRs) and neat central bathroom, front lounge and adjoining dining room, separate kitchen/meals. Features include a gas heater and air conditioner (in the lounge), high ceilings, polished floorboards, plus a wonderfully deep backyard with bungalow/studio, garage, shed and plenty of room to expand. A sensational location, the best of Coburg is at your fingertips including trains, trams and buses, renowned shops and major supermarkets, cafes and restaurants, easy access to local parks and schools - and all just 10kms from the city. First time offered in over 60 years - what an opportunity!
Land Size: 538sqm Approx
Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
